### Positive Patterns

- ✅ `AsSpan`-based `Concat` — used correctly in `FixedLengthTruncator` (left path) and `FixedNumberOfCharactersTruncator`
- ✅ Early-return guards — null/empty/already-fits checks avoid unnecessary work
- ✅ `DefaultTruncator` is a static singleton — no per-call allocation
- ✅ `??=` coalescing for `truncationString` — clean null handling

